headline: Paycom Software, Inc. Announces Third Quarter 2025 Earnings Release Date and Conference Call
summary: OKLAHOMA CITY, October 15, 2025--Paycom Software, Inc. ("Paycom") (NYSE: PAYC), a leading provider of comprehensive, cloud-based human capital management software, will release its results for the third quarter ended Sept. 30, 2025, after the market closes on Nov. 5. Paycom will also hold a conference call to discuss results at 5 p.m. (Eastern) that day.

headline: Paycom Reveals Record-High Cost of Manual HR Tasks, Based on EY Study
summary: OKLAHOMA CITY, October 15, 2025--Paycom Software, Inc. (NYSE: PAYC) ("Paycom"), a leading provider of comprehensive, cloud-based human capital management software, released updates to its usage management analytics tool, Direct Data Exchange®, based on an updated report from professional services firm EY, estimating the labor and nonlabor costs of common HR tasks.

headline: Where Does Paycom Stand After a 10% Slide and Mixed Analyst Forecasts?
summary: If you are looking at Paycom Software's recent stock performance and wondering what to do next, you are not alone. The decision to buy, hold, or sell has been tough for many investors after a stretch of both ups and downs. Just in the last week, shares have dipped by 1.6%, and in the past month the stock is down nearly 10%. Yet, zooming out reveals a different picture, with a strong 22.4% gain over the past year.
